                      <p>Spend two inspiring days aboard our RYA training yacht and <strong>learn to sail in Greece</strong> with a small group of fellow beginners or friends. This <strong>RYA Start Yachting course</strong> is designed to give you hands-on experience, teamwork skills, and a real sense of what it's like to sail with the wind.</p>
                      <p>Your yacht, <strong><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"  href="/yachts/lookfar"><u>Athena</u></a> ‚Äì a spacious Bavaria 44</strong> or <strong>‚ÄúAthena‚Äù ‚Äì a Bavaria 46 cruiser</strong>, is moored at Manoel Island Marina (Pontoon D, near Paparazzi Restaurant). Boarding begins at <strong>9:00 AM on the first day</strong> of the course.</p>
                      <p>Our experienced RYA-certified instructor will welcome you on board, guide you through a full <strong>yacht safety briefing</strong>, and ensure you're comfortable before heading out. Throughout the course, you'll learn key sailing techniques like steering, basic sail handling, ropework, and onboard safety practices. Even if it's your first time on a boat, you'll quickly feel empowered and part of the crew.</p>
